    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1975-08-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1975-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="99"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d99">
                <head>99. Memorandum From the Executive Secretary of the Economic Policy Board
                        (<persName corresp="#p_PRB1" type="from">Porter</persName>) to President
                        <persName corresp="#p_FGR1" type="to">Ford</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d99fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_FGR1"
                            >Ford</persName> Library, President’s Handwriting File, Subject File,
                        Box 19, Finance—Gold. No classification marking. Attached to an August 29
                        covering memorandum from <persName corresp="#p_CJ2">Connor</persName> to
                        President <persName corresp="#p_FGR1">Ford</persName> that reads: “<persName
                            corresp="#p_PRB1">Roger Porter</persName> sent this in per your
                        request.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1975-08-29">August 29, 1975</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Economic Policy Board Executive Committee Vote on U.S. Negotiating
                        Position on Gold</item>
                </list>
                <p>As Executive Secretary of the Economic Policy Board, I was designated by
                    Secretary <persName corresp="#p_SWE1">Simon</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_SLW1">Mr. Seidman</persName> to conduct the secret ballot you
                    requested at this morning’s Economic and Energy Meeting<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d99fn2">The meeting took place in the Cabinet Room from 11:15 a.m.
                        to 12:15 p.m. In attendance were President <persName corresp="#p_FGR1"
                            >Ford</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SWE1">Simon</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_SLW1">Seidman</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJ3">Dunlop</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_LJT1"
                            >Lynn</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BE2">Butz</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_IRS1">Ingersoll</persName>, Domestic Council Executive
                        Director and President’s Assistant for Domestic Affairs James Cannon III,
                        Morton, <persName corresp="#p_ETO1">Enders</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_YE1">Yeo</persName>, Domestic Council Deputy Director
                        Richard Dunham, <persName corresp="#p_GA1">Greenspan</persName>, Counselor
                            <persName corresp="#p_MJO1">John Marsh, Jr.</persName>, Federal Energy
                        Administration Administrator Frank Zarb, Counselor <persName
                            corresp="#p_HR2">Robert Hartmann</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_CR1"
                            >Cheney</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rumsfeld</persName>,
                        President’s Assistant for Legislative Affairs Max Friedersdorf, Press
                        Secretary Ronald Nessen, Assistant Press Secretary John Carlson, and
                            <persName corresp="#p_PRB1">Porter</persName>. (Ibid., President’s Daily
                        Diary) No other record of the meeting has been found.</note> on the issue of
                    the U.S. negotiating position on gold.</p>
                <pb facs="0356" n="325" xml:id="pg_325"/>
                <p>The closest refinement of the issue is as follows: <table cols="2" rows="2">
                        <row>
                            <cell>
                                <hi rend="italic">Treasury Position:</hi>
                            </cell>
                            <cell>Central banks should not be free to sell gold to one another for
                                the settlement of regular or normal transactions.</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>
                                <hi rend="italic">Federal Reserve Board Position:</hi>
                            </cell>
                            <cell>Central banks should not be free to sell gold to one another for
                                the settlement of regular or normal transactions <hi rend="italic"
                                    >and</hi> central bank transactions in gold must be restricted
                                to emergency circumstances.</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p>The votes of the Executive Committee members are as follows: <table cols="2"
                        rows="3">
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Treasury Position Supported by <persName corresp="#p_SWE1"
                                    >Simon</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_DJ3">Dunlop</persName>,
                                Morton, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>, <persName
                                    corresp="#p_SLW1">Seidman</persName>
                                <note n="3" xml:id="d99fn3">President <persName corresp="#p_FGR1"
                                        >Ford</persName> initialed his approval of this position.
                                        <persName corresp="#p_SLW1">Seidman</persName>, <persName
                                        corresp="#p_SWE1">Simon</persName>, <persName
                                        corresp="#p_PRB1">Porter</persName>, and <persName
                                        corresp="#p_RD1">Rumsfeld</persName> were apprised of the
                                    President’s decision that day, according to an August 29
                                    memorandum from <persName corresp="#p_CJ2">Connor</persName> to
                                        <persName corresp="#p_SLW1">Seidman</persName>. (Ibid.,
                                    President’s Handwriting File, Subject File, Box 19,
                                    Finance—Gold)</note>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Federal Reserve Board Position Supported by <persName
                                    corresp="#p_BA2">Burns</persName>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Abstentions: <persName corresp="#p_LJT1">Lynn</persName>,
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GA1">Greenspan</persName>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p>The Department of State vote was cast by Deputy Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_IRS1">Ingersoll</persName> who spoke with Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> following the meeting.</p>
            </div>
